        "created_at": "2019-11-03T19:26:53.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Was a tough year in Europe, but I popped a 65 Mouton with some board members several years ago at my house, it was was quite lovely.  And very surprisingly alive.  As was a recent 73 Latour, which was outstanding.  And a 66 Magdelaine.  I\u2019ve not had any CDP that old, but a 66 Hermitage from Delas that I had at Berns from 375 was also outstanding.  I\u2019ve had some decent luck here.</p>",
